## Existing Patterns to Follow

### Modal Pattern (from PATTERNS.md)
- Use `modalService.open(ModalNameE.ERROR, { message: string })` to trigger
- Use `modalService.close(ModalNameE.ERROR)` to dismiss
- Modal state managed in `GlobalStoreFieldE.MODALS`

### Component Structure (from COMPONENTS.md)
- Modal component uses HTML `<dialog>` element
- Props include: `name: ModalNameE`, `title: string`, `children: ReactNode`
- Uses `useGlobalValue(GlobalStoreFieldE.MODALS)` for state subscription

### Error Handling (from ARCHITECTURE.md)
- Axios interceptor is the appropriate place for global API error handling
- Services should transform errors to user-friendly messages

